"title": "4132: demons, malevolence of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4132: demons, malevolence of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Demons are opposed to the person and work of God and seek to lead human beings, including believers, away from him. For this reason, believers are forbidden to be involved with them.</p>\n<h2>Demons harm individuals</h2>\n<h3>Demons cause torment and pain</h3>\n<p>Saul's torment:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:14-1Sam16:16\">1SA 16:14–16:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:23\">1SA 16:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:10-1Sam18:11\">1SA 18:10–18:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:9-1Sam19:10\">1SA 19:9–19:10</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:22\">MAT 15:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:15\">MAT 17:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:18-Mark9:20\">MRK 9:18–9:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:39-Luke9:42\">LUK 9:39–9:42</a> <em>the boy with an evil spirit</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:5\">MRK 5:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:18\">LUK 6:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:11\">LUK 13:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:16\">ACT 5:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:16\">ACT 19:16</a> <em>the seven sons of Sceva</em></p>\n<h3>Demons cause dissension</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:23-Judg9:25\">JDG 9:23–9:25</a></p>\n<h3>Demons cause illness and handicaps</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:17-Mark9:27\">MRK 9:17–9:27</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:14-Matt17:18\">MAT 17:14–17:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:37-Luke9:42\">LUK 9:37–9:42</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:32-Matt9:33\">MAT 9:32–9:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:14\">LUK 11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:11\">LUK 13:11</a></p>\n<h2>Demons are deceitful</h2>\n<h3>Demons inspire false prophets</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:21-1Kgs22:23\">1KI 22:21–22:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:21-2Chr18:22\">2CH 18:21–18:22</a></p>\n<h3>Demons incite war</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:13-Rev16:14\">REV 16:13–16:14</a></p>\n<h3>Demons lead people away from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:1-1John4:6\">1JN 4:1–4:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:1-1Tim4:2\">1TI 4:1–4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:13-Rev16:14\">REV 16:13–16:14</a></p>\n<h2>The inspiration of pagan religions by demons</h2>\n<h3>Pagan gods are identified as demons</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:20-1Cor10:21\">1CO 10:20–10:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:16-Deut32:17\">DEU 32:16–32:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:36-Ps106:39\">PSA 106:36–106:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:20\">REV 9:20</a></p>\n<h3>Demons inhabit ruins of pagan cities</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:2\">REV 18:2</a></p>\n<h2>All involvement with spirits and mediums is forbidden</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:31\">LEV 19:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:18\">EXO 22:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:6\">LEV 20:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:27\">LEV 20:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:10-Deut18:14\">DEU 18:10–18:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer27:9\">JER 27:9</a></p>\n<h3>Witchcraft is identified as a work of the sinful nature</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:19-Gal5:20\">GAL 5:19–5:20</a></p>\n<h3>Involvement with sorcery or witchcraft is futile</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:9\">ISA 47:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:7\">1SA 28:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:14-1Sam28:20\">1SA 28:14–28:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:19-Isa8:22\">ISA 8:19–8:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:3-Isa19:4\">ISA 19:3–19:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:12-Isa47:15\">ISA 47:12–47:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:3-Nah3:4\">NAM 3:3–3:4</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of renunciation of the work of demons</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:19\">ACT 19:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:9\">1SA 28:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:24\">2KI 23:24</a></p>",
